12:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Coderabbit and JetBrains AI share a solid foundation of core features including Debugging, Refactoring, Multi Language, Chat. Where Coderabbit pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Code Review, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on this capability. On the other hand, JetBrains AI uniquely offers Autocomplete and Code Generation and Test Generation and Ide Integration and Documentation, giving it an edge for users who prioritize these areas. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Coderabbit holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 8/10, while JetBrains AI scores 7/10 overall and 8/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
13:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, JetBrains AI comes in at a lower starting price of $10/mo, while Coderabbit begins at $12/mo. Coderabbit has a notable advantage here with its free plan, allowing you to get started without any financial commitment. JetBrains AI does not currently offer a free tier, which means you will need to pay from day one."}]]}]
