16:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Coderabbit is best suited for teams wanting automated PR reviews, maintaining code quality, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. JetBrains AI, meanwhile, shines for JetBrains IDE users, Java/Kotlin developers, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2023, Coderabbit describes itself as \"AI-powered code review for pull requests.\" JetBrains AI, established in 2023, positions itself as \"AI assistant built into JetBrains IDEs.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
17:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **JetBrains AI** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to more features (9 vs 5), more competitive pricing. However, this does not mean Coderabbit is a poor choice — far from it. Coderabbit excels in its own right, particularly for teams wanting automated PR reviews and maintaining code quality.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value deep jetbrains ide integration, go with JetBrains AI. If excellent pr review quality matters more to you, Coderabbit is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
